{
  "doc_id": "12804",
  "text": "In terms of productivity in suspension culture, the published data indicate that LV titers are similar to the values obtained in adherent cells. The titers achieved in the bulk harvest or culture supernatants are in the range of 10 7 to 10 8 infectious genomes (IG)/ml or TU/ml [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] while the productivity of adherent cell systems varies from 10 6 to 10 8 TU/ml [CITATION_4] (Table 1) . However, the comparison is rather difficult since a limited number of comparative studies has been reported using the same vector and because of differing analytical procedures.",
